This paper discusses the problem of Few-Shot Learning (FSL) in artificial intelligence, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of arXiv CS. Specifically, FSL involves machine learning techniques for generalizing from a limited number of examples, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, as they are the most general and encompass a wide range of topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The other sub-categories are also relevant because FSL has applications in computer vision, natural language processing, and other areas where limited data is a common challenge.
